  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- participatory action (survivor led response) on assessment, response planning, implementation and etc.
- tracking and documentation of IDPs
- emergency response - cash to SHGs/IDPs
- capacity building among IDPs and ECOWEB staff on IDP rights and advocacy
- regular coordination among CSOs and engagement with government</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- suffering of IDPs in evacuation centers, holding areas or temporary homes are reduced
- co-designed and implemented emergency response with IDPs
- coordinating mechanism between CSOs and Office of Civil Defence/NDRRMC established and strengthened
- IDPs rights protected</narrative>
  </description>
